    "comment": "Worldsim franka-libero-v1 (Newton/MuJoCo) reproduction of the LIBERO Franka Panda embodiment, for evaluating pi0.5 (lerobot/pi05_libero_finetuned_v044) and other LIBERO-trained VLAs. Delta end-effector control (ee_del): 7-DoF OSC_POSE eef delta (position scaled 0.05 m, axis-angle scaled 0.5 rad) + gripper (>0 closes), applied through a damped-least-squares IK approximation of robosuite's OSC_POSE (see sim/control.py). State is the absolute eef pose (position + axis-angle) + gripper finger qpos (ee_abs), deliberately mapped into LIBERO's world frame (STATE_POS_OFFSET / STATE_ORI_OFFSET_QUAT in control.py) so the values land in the checkpoint's normalization distribution — hence the stats here are the physical-intelligence/libero values, identical to demos libero_ee_del.json. Two 256x256 RGB views: observation/image=agentview (frontal third-person), observation/wrist_image=wrist (eye-in-hand). control_rate=20 Hz (sim dt 0.002, decimation 25); the env-side image/state values are raw (uint8 HWC frames, unnormalized state) — the policy applies its own normalization. OPEN: camera poses + table/base frame are not metrically aligned to LIBERO (sim-to-sim transfer knob, see scenes/franka-libero-v1/scene.xml); image orientation is rendered native (no 180-deg rotation) — verify against the training distribution if transfer is weak."
